<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="jn1015a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn1" href="#jn1015">JN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/jn1all.htm#jn1015a"> (NLI.2A) 15(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <p class="set">Still to be neat, still to be drest, <br>As you were going to a feast; <br>Still to be powder&apos;d, still perfumed: <br>Lady, it is to be presumed, <br>Though art&apos;s hid causes are not found, <br>All is not sweet, all is not sound.</p> <p class="set">Give me a look, give me a face, <br>That makes simplicity a grace; <br>Robes loosely flowing, hair as free: <br>Such sweet neglect more taketh me, <br>Than all the adulteries of art; <br>They strike mine eyes, but not my heart.</p> <p class="diip"> <u>Ben Johnson</u></p> <p class="spbr">(Jean Bonnefons &ldquo;Pancharis&rdquo;)</p> </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: <cite>The Works of Ben Jonson</cite>, ed. William Gifford (London: Nicol, 1816), <a href="https://archive.org/details/worksofbenjonson03jonsuoft/page/346/mode/2up" target="_blank">Vol. III: &ldquo;The Silent Woman&rdquo;, pp. 347f</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
